SIMPLE: footed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Footed
<hw>Foot"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a foot or feet;
shaped in the foot; <as>as, a <ex>footed</ex> candlestick</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Footed</xex> like a goat.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Grew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Footed</xex> is often used in composition in the
sense of <xex>having</xex> (<xex>such</xex> or <xex>so many</xex>)
<xex>feet</xex>; as, four<xex>footed</xex> beasts.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a foothold; established.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our king . . . is <qex>footed</qex> in this land already.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-footer</ent>⟦br⟧
